        <div class="badge-soft mb-2">Tourist Places</div>
        <h2 class="fw-bold mb-1">Must-visit destinations in Maharashtra</h2>
        <p class="text-muted mb-0">
            A curated list of famous cities, hill stations, beaches and heritage sites across the state.
        </p>
    </div>
    <a href="index.jsp" class="btn btn-outline-secondary d-none d-md-inline-flex">Back to Home</a>
    </div>

<div class="row g-4">
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3881104/pexels-photo-3881104.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Gateway of India and Mumbai skyline">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Mumbai</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    The capital city of Maharashtra, known as the financial capital of India. Explore
                    the Gateway of India, Marine Drive, Elephanta Caves, film city, beaches and vibrant nightlife.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/1005766/pexels-photo-1005766.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Hill station view of Mahabaleshwar">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Mahabaleshwar</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    A popular hill station in the Western Ghats, famous for its cool climate, strawberry farms,
                    viewpoints like Arthur’s Seat and Venna Lake for boating.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/1532771/pexels-photo-1532771.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Sandy beach and palm trees">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Konkan Beaches</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    The Konkan coastline is dotted with serene beaches like Ganpatipule, Tarkarli and Alibaug,
                    offering clean sands, water sports and delicious coastal food.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/355241/pexels-photo-355241.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Historic fort in the hills">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Forts of Maharashtra</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    Historical forts like Raigad, Sinhagad, Pratapgad and Shivneri narrate the stories
                    of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj and the Maratha empire, and offer scenic trekking routes.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/258945/pexels-photo-258945.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Ancient rock-cut cave">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Ajanta &amp; Ellora Caves</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    UNESCO World Heritage Sites near Aurangabad, famous for rock-cut Buddhist, Hindu and Jain
                    cave temples with intricate sculptures and paintings dating back to 2nd century BCE.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/167404/pexels-photo-167404.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Green hills with waterfalls in monsoon">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Lonavala &amp; Khandala</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    Twin hill stations near Pune and Mumbai, especially beautiful during monsoon with
                    lush greenery, waterfalls, dams and viewpoints like Tiger Point.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

